<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9783d57-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s5604"><num value="5604">§ 5604.</num><heading> Fines on ocean carriers</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Postal Service may impose or remit fines on carriers transporting mail by vessel on routes extending beyond the borders of the United States for—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb9783d58-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s5604/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> unreasonable or unnecessary delay to the mails; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb9783d59-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s5604/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> other delinquencies in the transportation of mail.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb9783d5a-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/773">84 Stat. 773</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb9783d5b-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb9783d5c-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb9783d5d-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1971-07-01">July 1, 1971</date>, pursuant to Resolution No. 71–9 of the Board of Governors. See <ref href="/us/pl/91/375/s15/a">section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, set out as a note preceding <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
